State.Description: On ancient ages, when neither the Blades had appeared yet, groups of annonymous honorable and strong men raised their weapons against the tyranny of dragons, when almost all still saw them as mighty gods to be venerated. This men are bound in destiny with dragons and with this last ones returning, their past slayers are coming back again too.
State.Name: Ancient Skeletons- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Aurochs are a large species of cattle that lives in big herds on Skyrim's tundra. They are wild animals that can't be tamed and are known to have a very aggressive behaviour, with killing one being seen as an act of courage in nordic culture. Wild Horses are a small breed of horse that also lives in large groups on the whiterun hold plains.
State.Name: Aurochs and Wild Horses - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Name: Bards Reborn Student of Song Become a Bard Expansion with Bard Spells

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Cockatrices are big flying chimeras resembling a draconic rooster or chicken, created by powerfull alchemists. The process is clouded in mistery, but is known that they born of eggs laid by roosters consorting with roosters, then the egg must be incubated by a toad or snake, which is devoured by the beast when he hatches.
State.Name: Cockatrices- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Cursed Child's Dolls are a type of Poltergeist, in common sense Poltergeists are an artificial type of half-independent entity created unconsciously by sentient mortal beings, as a response to feelings like fear or anger. They commonly possess objects and corrupt them, in this case they turned dolls into bloody killer toys.
State.Name: Cursed Child's Doll - 2017 Halloween Special (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ideal for hunters, this mod adds 6 new species and 12 varieties of Deer to Skyrim, expanding substantially the presence of this kind of herbivores on the province.
State.Name: Deer Expansion - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Among the ranks of Draugrs you'll find the fearsome Draugr Horsemen. Ages ago they were the valorous members of the cavalry on the nordic society, but nowadays, undead and accursed to never find rest, they still patrol the exterior areas of their dungeons, rinding their mummified Helhests, searching for intruders.
State.Name: Draugr Cavalry- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dugongs and Manatees are aquatic peacefull herbivorous mammals, that inhabit lakes, estuaries and coastal marine waters. Three varieties exist in Skyrim, the small Manatee, the larger Dugong and the giant Sea Cow. All the 3 are massively hunted by nords for their meat, oil and fat.
State.Name: Dugongs and Manatees - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ettins are abominations with two-heads and an immense fury for all living beings. Descendants of an ogre tribe cursed by Malacath himself in remote ages, these tormented beasts of incredible strength, but limited intellect, are all that an adventurer does not want to encounter.
State.Name: Ettins - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Created by the Fire Lords in the deep boilers of flaming lava in the realm of Infernace, these Flame Atronachs are true living storms of fire and igneous rock. Made in the image and likeness of the powerful Storm Atronachs, scholars claim that Flame Turmoils even surpass those in which they were inspired.
State.Name: Flame Turmoils- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Giant Centipedes are enormous and lenghty insect-like monsters, whith hard chitinous armor covering nearly the entire body. Sticking out from under this carapace are rows of hooked limbs. They have various pairs of long antennae, 2 pairs of sharp mandibles and 1 pair of frontal big pincer-like limbs that they use to catch prey.
State.Name: Giant Centipedes- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Giant Sloths are large lumbering mammals native from the forests of Valenwood, the savannas of Elsweyr and the tundra of Skyrim. They are related to the small arboreal sloths, and passive unless provoked. The herbivore Glyptodonts are heavy armored mammals related  and similar to armadillos, with the size of a carriage, though flatter in shape.
State.Name: Giant Sloths and Glyptodonts- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Giant snakes are large and extremely poisonous reptiles, that occasionally eat small boats and were rarely seen on land. Widely hunted, today their numbers have reduced, and so have their size, but they are still dangerous enemies and the terror of any unwary adventurer, that they manage to ambush , with their slithering cunning.
State.Name: Giant Snakes - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Gorgonops are agile small reptomammals, with powerfull large jaws and teeth. Two species inhabit skyrim, the smaller spotted Lycaenops, that hunts in packs on the tundra, with the size of a small fox, and the solitary Gorgonops, bigger, and only seem on the volcanic area of Eastmarsh.
State.Name: Gorgonops - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Reptilians from the provinces of Morrowind and Black Marsh, Guars are the primary domesticated herd animal of these provinces, and are usually docile and not aggressive. Characterized by their endurance, Guars are used mostly as pack animals and beasts of burden, and mounts, by the Dunmer and the Argonian.
State.Name: Guars- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Name: Riekrs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Silt Striders are gargantuan arthropods native to Morrowind. They have stilt-like legs, and a body resembling the curved and armored body of a flea. They are a resilient species whose tough carapace helps them survive the adverse environment of the province. The Dunmer domesticated the gigantic arthropods long ago, using them for transportation.
State.Name: Silt Striders - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)
